  <div class="container">
    <h1>RPen</h1>
    <p class="intro">
      The RPen is a precision thermal tool designed for repairing or reapplying thermoplastic bonds. Powered by USB-C and built with a custom resistive heating PCB, it enables clean, controlled heat application without the need for buttons or software.
    </p>

    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Power:</strong> 5 V via USB-C (safe negotiation using CC pull-down resistors)</li>
      <li><strong>Heating Surface:</strong> Copper serpentine trace on FR-4 or polyimide</li>
      <li><strong>Performance:</strong> Reaches ~150 °C in approximately 5 minutes at 2.5 W</li>
      <li><strong>Operation:</strong> Passive — no switches, no interface, no active control</li>
      <li><strong>Safety:</strong> Labeled heating pad with clear warnings: “DO NOT TOUCH / NO TOUCH ZONE”</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <p>
      To use the RPen, simply plug it into a USB-C power source. The heating element will begin warming up immediately. After a few minutes, it's ready to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Soften and undo existing thermoplastic bonds (like Loyal Adhesive capsules)</li>
      <li>Melt new adhesive directly on the pad and apply it for clean resealing</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Design Philosophy</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Minimalism:</strong> No buttons, screens, or software — just plug and act</li>
      <li><strong>Intentional Use:</strong> Designed to support slow, careful restoration work</li>
      <li><strong>Discreet Aesthetics:</strong> Professional look with understated branding</li>
    </ul>
